[30;1m55 | [0m[35m=============================[0m

[30;1m86 | [0m[35mRate limiting[0m
[30;1m87 | [0m[35m-------------[0m
[30;1m88 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m89 | [0m[35mAirflow can be configured to limit the number of authentication requests in a given time window. We [0m
[30;1m90 | [0m[35m`Flask-Limiter <https://flask-limiter.readthedocs.io/en/stable/>`_ to achieve that and by default Ai[0m
[30;1m91 | [0m[35muses per-webserver default limit of 5 requests per 40 second fixed window. By default no common stor[0m
[30;1m92 | [0m[35mrate limits is used between the gunicorn processes you run so rate-limit is applied separately for e[0m
